      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pre-heat your oven to 180°C/356°F."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your potatoes into small chunks. Separate your cloves of garlic from the bulb and peel them all."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tip your potatoes and garlic into a large roasting tray. Pick the leaves off the rosemary and scatter these in too. Drizzle with a good glug of olive oil and a sprinkle of salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roast for 25 mins, then take them out of the oven and give them a flip. Return them to the oven for another 25 mins until perfectly golden and crispy."
